cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Artefaux: A Deterministic ECG Noise and Lead-Failure Stress-Test Corpus"
abstract: >-
  A richly-labelled, deterministically reproducible stress-test corpus and
  generation engine for validating ECG signal-quality gates and noise detectors.
  Artefaux mixes real recorded noise (MIT-BIH NSTDB) into clean 12-lead ECGs
  (PTB-XL) and adds engineered electrode-domain and lead-failure corruptions to
  systematically exercise signal-processing robustness. It is a stress-test set,
  not a clinically representative cohort.
message: >-
  If you use Artefaux, please cite it as below and additionally cite the source
  datasets (PTB-XL, PTB-XL+, MIT-BIH NSTDB, MACECGDB) as documented in
  ATTRIBUTION.md.
type: software
license: GPL-3.0-or-later
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-07-13"
authors:
